Taiwan Stocks: Cathay, Polaris, Taiwan Semiconductor

-- B y   A d e l a   L i n
-- 
2011-04-11T06:16:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/taiwan-stocks-htc-polaris-taiwan-semiconductor-yuanta.html
(Corrects currency of profit estimate in Cathay item.)  Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Taiwan  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 1:30 p.m. close.  The Taiex Index dropped 14.27, or 0.2 percent, to 8,880.27.  Cathay Financial Holding Co. (2882 TT), Taiwan’s largest
publicly traded financial service company, fell 2.3 percent to
NT$46.45, the biggest decline since March 15. It posted first-
quarter net income of NT$1.85 billion ($64 million), the company
said in a statement to the Taiwan stock exchange. The median
forecast in a Bloomberg survey of five analysts was for profit
of NT$3.515 billion.  HTC Corp. (2498)  (2498 TT),  Asia ’s second-largest smartphone maker
by market value, climbed 3.5 percent to NT$1,200 after the
company posted record sales and profit for the first quarter as
demand for more-advanced handsets boosted revenue.  Polaris Securities Co. (2854 TT) added 1.2 percent to
NT$20.85, the highest level since May 2, 2008, after the Taipei-
based broker agreed to be acquired by Yuanta Financial Holding
Co. (2885 TT). Yuanta, which will pay 0.5 shares and NT$12.2 in
cash for each Polaris stock, fell 3.5 percent to NT$20.65.  Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co. (2330 TT), the
world’s largest custom manufacturer of chips, lost 2.5 percent
to NT$71.1, the steepest loss since March 15, after posting
consolidated first-quarter revenue of NT$105.4 billion, less
than the NT$106.7 billion average of 20 analyst estimates
compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:  To contact the reporter on this story:
